Install acme.sh

curl https://get.acme.sh | sh

register zerossl account with eab-kid and eab-hmac-key

Current EAB_KID AND EAB_HMAC_KEY

EAB_KID = IHaqnTbx6CyzmP0PlS1nCg

EAB_HMAC_KEY = NYKtkJvUzG7s6deHSyXkNz2YfQ7EDldpYHsHN8cLzzf6RiF8e6c_adXLlHZckBQY8IhkG6zWpVzpOuTeuKN5Cg

acme.sh --register-account --server zerossl --eab-kid IHaqnTbx6CyzmP0PlS1nCg --eab-hmac-key NYKtkJvUzG7s6deHSyXkNz2YfQ7EDldpYHsHN8cLzzf6RiF8e6c_adXLlHZckBQY8IhkG6zWpVzpOuTeuKN5Cg

You can generate EAB credentials in zerossl. it is important not to generate again as we will need to update the current EAB credentials in 



create /var/www/_letsencrypt directory and add the configuration on nginx/openresty conf file.

mkdir /var/www/_letsencrypt -p;

# Nginx Configuration
# ACME-challenge
location ^~ /.well-known/acme-challenge/ {
    root /var/www/_letsencrypt;
}


install the certificate to its path

acme.sh --install-cert -d mydomain.com --key-file  /software/ssl/mydomain.com/mydomain.com.key  --fullchain-file /software/ssl/mydomain.com/mydomain.com.crt


check if the configuration is correct using openresty -t or nginx -t

reload openresty/nginx or run tb
